author: CNN
description:
CNN Political Director David Chalian breaks down the recent Democratic victories in Miami and Georgia and what these results could mean for the party’s momentum heading into the 2026 elections.

author: CNN
description: Italy has a very tasty reason to celebrate: Its national cuisine has become the first entire gastronomic style to be recognized by UNESCO, the UN’s cultural body — a status that should help protect it from imitators. The decision to designate Italian food as an intangible cultural heritage was confirmed on Wednesday by Italian Prime Minister Giorgia Meloni ahead of an announcement expected from UNESCO. The status marks the successful end to a three-year campaign by Italy’s Agriculture Ministry to have the nation’s traditional way of growing, harvesting, preparing and serving food recognized. #CNN #News
title: Italian cuisine becomes world's first to be awarded UNESCO status

author: CNN
description: CNN's Jake Tapper takes a look at President Donald Trump's remarks on Tuesday referring to African nations as "shithole countries," and how his comments confirm the president's reported use of the word in 2018, an allegation he denied at the time.
title: Trump confirms he thinks African countries are "shitholes"

author: CNN
description: US Secretary of State Marco Rubio ordered diplomats to return to using Times New Roman font in official communications, calling his predecessor Antony Blinken’s decision to adopt Calibri a “wasteful” diversity move, according to an internal department cable seen by Reuters.
title: Rubio brings back Times New Roman font, ousting “wasteful” Calibri

author: CNN
description:
President Donald Trump confirmed that the US has taken control of an oil tanker off the coast of Venezuela.

“As you probably know we’ve just seized a tanker on the coast of Venezuela,” Trump said. “Large tanker, very large, largest one ever seized, actually.”

The president did not offer any immediate explanation for the move, which is likely to further escalate tensions with the South American nation.           #CNN #News
title: Trump says US seized oil tanker off Venezuelan coast

author: CNN
description: The Federal Reserve lowered interest rates again in a continued effort to keep the labor market intact, despite objections from several key Fed officials who believe the central bank should be prioritizing the higher cost of living instead.                                                                                                            #CNN #News
title: Fed lowers interest rates for the third time in a row and projects just one cut next year

author: CNN
description: The Indianapolis Colts brought 44-year-old quarterback Philip Rivers out of retirement to join the practice squad. If he plays with the Colts this Sunday, he would be NFL’s oldest player. CNN’s Andy Scholes reports. #cnn #news #indianapoliscolts
title: Philip Rivers comes out of retirement to join Colts

author: CNN
description: "We have seen it across the political map, whereby over and over and over again, the baseline from 2024, Democrats are consistently outperforming it." CNN chief data analyst Harry Enten looks at the results of the Miami mayoral race, President Trump's net approval among Latinos, and the number of GOP mayors in the 50 largest US cities. Manu Raju also discusses with his "Inside Politics" panel: the Atlanta Journal-Constitution's Washington bureau chief Tia Mitchell, CNN political director David Chalian and CNN chief domestic correspondent Phil Mattingly. #CNN #News
title: What Miami's mayoral win means for Dems: Harry Enten runs the numbers

author: CNN
description:
Federal agents used pepper spray to disperse a crowd of protesters that surrounded their vehicles in a heavily Somali neighborhood in Minnesota. The Trump administration has been openly targeting the Somali community with immigration enforcement operations. ICE officials told the AP via email that they made no arrests in the neighborhood and provided no further details.

#cnn #news #immigration #somali #minneapolis #trump
title: Protesters confront ICE agents in Minneapolis neighborhood

author: CNN
description:
Following President Donald Trump’s claim that Ukraine is “losing” the war against Russia’s ongoing invasion and that Moscow now has the “upper hand,” multiple officials told CNN there are no new US or European assessments suggesting there have been significant changes on the battlefield and they don’t see any indications President Vladimir Putin’s forces are likely to win the conflict quickly. Ukraine is ready to hold elections in the next 60 to 90 days if its allies can guarantee security for the vote, President Volodymyr Zelensky said Tuesday. Following a meeting with European leaders this week, Zelensky said he expects Ukraine will hand over an updated peace proposal to the US on Wednesday.

CNN correspondent Clare Sebastian and CNN chief national security analyst Jim Sciutto report. #CNN #News
title: Zelensky: We do not have the strength to retake Crimea

description: Eileen Higgins will be the next mayor of the city of Miami, according to a projection from CNN’s Decision Desk, breaking a nearly 30-year Republican streak in holding the nonpartisan seat and giving Democrats another example of strong performance in elections during the first year of President Donald Trump’s second term. title: Why a short trip in the West Bank can take all day

description:

Join the community to share your story and watch Anderson's weekly streaming show All There Is Live at https://cnn.com/allthereis

author: CNN
description: The Senate will vote Thursday to try and address rising health care costs for many Americans after enhanced Affordable Care Act tax credits enacted in 2021 expire at the end of this year. On Tuesday, Majority Leader John Thune announced that the Senate will vote on a Republican-led alternative to the Democrats’ proposed three-year extension of the enhanced tax credits. Neither bill, however, is expected to get the 60 votes needed to advance.
title: Republican senators sound the alarm on health care costs
